Sentencas: Perovskite oxides with mixed electronic-ionic conduction are important catalysts for the oxygen reduction reaction in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Structures and Properties of LaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ and BaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ as Cobalt-Free Perovskite-Type Cathode Materials for the Oxygen Reduction Reaction

Sentencas: Here, two cobalt-free perovskite oxides, LaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta (LFCuO) and BaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta (BFCuO), were synthesized and comparatively studied with respect to their phase structures, oxygen contents, chemical defects, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), as well as electrical and electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Structures and Properties of LaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ and BaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ as Cobalt-Free Perovskite-Type Cathode Materials for the Oxygen Reduction Reaction

Sentencas: Different structures and properties have been found for each oxide, which have been interpreted based on their tolerance factors and chemical defects.
Titulo: Structures and Properties of LaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ and BaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ as Cobalt-Free Perovskite-Type Cathode Materials for the Oxygen Reduction Reaction

Sentencas: LFCuO showed much better overall performance than BFCuO, and it proved to be a promising cobalt-free cathode material of intermediate-temperature SOFCs with a low TEC (12.0 x 10(6) C-1) that matches well with TECs of the electrolytes, high catalytic activity for the oxygen reduction reaction characterized by low area specific resistances (0.090 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 020 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C), and high-temperature chemical stability with electrolytes.
Titulo: Structures and Properties of LaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ and BaFe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ as Cobalt-Free Perovskite-Type Cathode Materials for the Oxygen Reduction Reaction
